itemDescription: English composer specializing in chamber music

wikipedia_page.main: Nicholas (Nick) Casswell (born 1974) is an English composer specializing in chamber music.

response: *2007: First prize: Nicholas Casswell (Great Britain), second prize: Robert Lemay (Canada), third prize: Akihiro Kano (Japan), fourth prize: Gordon Hamilton (Australia)."Activities 2007", Luxembourg Music Information Centre. Retrieved 12 January 2011.

*"International Composition Prize Luxembourg 2007, World Premiere Recordings": Nicholas Casswell, "Triplicity"; Robert Lemay, "Mare Tranquilitatis III"; Akihiro Kano, "The Fifth Station"; Gordon Hamilton, "Sinfonietta Concertante". Luxembourg Sinfonietta, Conductor: Marcel Wengler. CD LGNM No 407.
